    <body>
        <p>Erratum “Table of Content”, CONVERGENCE 18(1), February
            2012. </p>
        <p>The following two research articles were wrongly referred to as articles.</p>
        <p>1] Keeping it real: Encountering mixed reality in igloo’s
            <italic>SwanQuake: House,</italic> by Sita Popat, DOI: <related-article ext-link-type="doi" id="ra1-10.1177_0269881110381185" page="11" related-article-type="corrected-article" vol="18" xlink:href="10.1177/1354856511419913" xlink:type="simple"/> 10.1177/1354856511419913</p>
        <p>2] Comparing situated sense-making processes in virtual worlds: Application of
            Dervin’s Sense-Making Methodology to media reception Situations, by CarrieLynn D.
            Reinhard and Brenda Dervin, DOI: <related-article ext-link-type="doi" id="ra2-10.1177_0269881110381185" page="27" related-article-type="corrected-article" vol="18" xlink:href="10.1177/1354856511419914" xlink:type="simple"/> 10.1177/1354856511419914</p>
        <p>SAGE apologizes to readers for the error; the contributions by Sita Popat and CarrieLynn
            D. Reinhard/Brenda Dervin are and should have been listed as ‘Research
            articles' as they underwent our formal peer review process prior to
            publication.</p>
